results.name: Decimal expansion of 1/79.
comment: The 13-digit cycle 1, 0, 1, 2, 6, 5, 8, 2, 2, 7, 8, 4, 8 in this sequence and the others based on seventy-ninths, gives the successive digits of the smallest integer which is multiplied by eight when the final digit is moved from the right hand end to the left hand end. - _Ian Duff_, Jan 09 2009
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
